    <div class="post-entry  blockquote-style-1">
        <div class="inner-post-entry entry-content" id="penci-post-entry-inner">

			<i class="penci-post-countview-number-check" style="display:none">633</i>
			
<p>The M6 World Championship reached a thrilling high with the knockout stage matches on December 7 and 8, 2024. Another day, another stage for all the teams that pass to the knockout stage! Congratulations to all 8 teams that threw their spirit successfully to the next stage! This pivotal phase marked the beginning of the double-elimination bracket, where only the strongest teams would survive to continue their journey toward the Grand Finals. The tension was palpable as each match was a battle of wits, reflexes, and unyielding determination.<br></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-recalc-dims="1" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" data-attachment-id="49367" data-permalink="https://news.seagm.com/recap-m6-mlbb-championship-knockout-stage/beige_minimalist_linear_face_illustration_makeup_studio_facebook_cover/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?fit=1640%2C924&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="1640,924" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?fit=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?fit=1024%2C577&amp;ssl=1" src="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?resize=1024%2C577&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-49367" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?resize=1024%2C577&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?resize=768%2C433&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?resize=1536%2C865&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?resize=1200%2C676&amp;ssl=1 1200w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?resize=1170%2C659&amp;ssl=1 1170w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?resize=585%2C330&amp;ssl=1 585w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Beige_Minimalist_Linear_Face_Illustration_Makeup_Studio_Facebook_Cover.png?w=1640&amp;ssl=1 1640w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure>



<p>On December 7, the intense competition unfolded with the first round of best-of-three (BO3) matches. The long-standing rivalry between FNOP and SRG continued in the M6 World Championship knockout stage. This time, FNOP emerged victorious, securing a 2-0 sweep over SRG. With this win, FNOP advances to the Upper Bracket semi-final, where they will face FCON. Meanwhile, SRG has been relegated to the Lower Bracket, where they must fight for survival. Despite the defeat, SRG’s coach said they learn from their mistakes and will prepare the best for the comeback after their hero composition is only tailored on first-game strategy during the knockout stage. FNOP’s EXP Laner, Kirk, displayed exceptional skill by flawlessly executing a game-changing performance with his comfort hero, Edith.<br></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img data-recalc-dims="1" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" data-attachment-id="49368" data-permalink="https://news.seagm.com/recap-m6-mlbb-championship-knockout-stage/dsc08526/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?fit=6000%2C3376&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="6000,3376" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="DSC08526" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?fit=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?fit=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1" src="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-49368" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?resize=1536%2C864&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?resize=2048%2C1152&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?resize=1200%2C675&amp;ssl=1 1200w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?resize=1920%2C1080&amp;ssl=1 1920w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?resize=1170%2C658&amp;ssl=1 1170w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?resize=585%2C329&amp;ssl=1 585w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?w=2340&amp;ssl=1 2340w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DSC08526.jpg?w=3510&amp;ssl=1 3510w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure>



<p>Team Vamos’ journey at the M6 World Championship has come to a bittersweet end as they were sent to the Lower Bracket after a crushing defeat. The hopes of seeing a Malaysian showdown in the final, where two homegrown teams would battle for supremacy, have now been dashed. With this loss, Team Vamos’ dream of reaching the grand stage has slipped further away. Their spot in the Lower Bracket means they must now fight their way through a grueling set of elimination matches.<br></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img data-recalc-dims="1" decoding="async" width="844" height="398" data-attachment-id="49371" data-permalink="https://news.seagm.com/recap-m6-mlbb-championship-knockout-stage/untitled-design-1-7/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Untitled-design-1.png?fit=844%2C398&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="844,398" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Untitled design (1)" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Untitled-design-1.png?fit=300%2C141&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Untitled-design-1.png?fit=844%2C398&amp;ssl=1" src="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Untitled-design-1.png?resize=844%2C398&amp;ssl=1" alt="" class="wp-image-49371" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Untitled-design-1.png?w=844&amp;ssl=1 844w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Untitled-design-1.png?resize=300%2C141&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Untitled-design-1.png?resize=768%2C362&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/news.seagm.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Untitled-design-1.png?resize=585%2C276&amp;ssl=1 585w" sizes="(max-width: 844px) 100vw, 844px"></figure>



<p>The stage is set for an epic showdown in the Upper Bracket Final of the M6 World Championship, where FNOP will face off against TLID. Both MPL PH and MPL ID champions are set to bring the heat in this crucial match. The stakes couldn’t be higher, as the loser will have to return to their hometown, leaving their dreams of the M6 World Championship shattered. Meanwhile, the Lower Bracket is heating up, as the teams are fighting for their chance to reclaim glory.</p>
